                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.2.1">
                           <locus from="8v" to="11v"/>
                           <title type="complete">List of the kings of Ethiopia until the reign of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10303Yekunno">Yǝkunno ʾAmlāk</persName>
                           </title>
                           <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                        </msItem>
                      
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.2.2">
                           <locus from="12r" to="20r"/>
                           <title type="complete">List of the successors of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10303Yekunno">Yǝkunno ʾAmlāk</persName> and summaries of the events of their reigns, 
                          until the death of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6229LebnaDe">Lǝbna Dǝngǝl</persName>
                           </title>
                           <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                           <note>
                          The following is the list of the successors of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10303Yekunno">Yǝkunno ʾAmlāk</persName>:
                          <p>
                                 <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10303Yekunno">Yǝkunno ʾAmlāk</persName> reigned for 15 years. </p>
                              <p>
                                 <persName xml:lang="gez" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10215Yagbas">ያግብአ፡ ጽዮን፡</persName> reigned for nine years.</p>
                              <p>
                                 <persName xml:lang="gez" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5326hezbaAs">ሕዝበ፡ አስገድ፡</persName>, <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS8029QedmaAs">ቅድመ፡ አስገድ፡</persName>,
                         <persName xml:lang="gez" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS8757senfaAr">ጽንፈ፡ አርዓድ፡</persName> and their two brothers reigned for five years. </p>
                              <p>
                                 <persName xml:lang="gez" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10111WedemR">ውድም፡ አርዓድ፡</persName> reigned for 15 years.</p>
                              <p>
                                 <persName xml:lang="gez" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS1854Amdase">ዓምደ፡ ጽዮን፡</persName> reigned for thirty years. 
                            <q xml:lang="en">He was suddenly attacked by ten kings at a time when he had not assembled his army. He fought and defeated them. <gap reason="omitted" extent="unknown" resp="PRS10747Zotenbe"/>
                                 </q>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                 <persName xml:lang="gez" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS8595SayfaAr">ሰይፈ፡ አርዓድ፡</persName> reigned for 28 years.</p>
                              <p>   His son <persName xml:lang="gez" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7559NewayaM">ውድም፡ አስፈሬ፡</persName> reigned for ten years.</p>
                              <p> 
                                 <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS3429DawitII">Dāwit II</persName> reigned for 29 years. 
                           <q xml:lang="en">Under his reign the glorious cross of Our Lord Jesus Christ
                             appeared, which caused miracles before hima and his troups <gap reason="omitted" extent="unknown" resp="PRS10747Zotenbe"/>
                                 </q>
                                 <q xml:lang="gez">ውእቱኒ፡ ተመጠዎ፡ በክብር፡ ወበሥርዓተ፡ መንግሥት።</q>
                              </p>
                              <p> 
                                 <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS9429Tewodros">Tewodros I</persName> reigned for three years. </p>
                              <p>
                                 <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10342Yeshaq">Yǝsḥāq</persName> reigned for 15 years. 
                          <q xml:lang="en">In the tenth year of his reign the 13th cycle came to an end.
                            From <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10303Yekunno">Yǝkunno ʾAmlāk</persName> until this time, 54 years had elapsed, and altogether <supplied reason="explanation" resp="PRS10747Zotenbe">since creation</supplied> 6917 years.</q>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                 <persName xml:lang="gez" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS3790endreyas">እንድርያስ፡</persName>, the son of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10342Yeshaq">Yǝsḥāq</persName> reigned for six months.</p>
                              <p>
                                 <persName xml:lang="gez" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS9175TaklaMa">ሕዝበ፡ ናኝ፡</persName> and <persName xml:lang="gez" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS1843AmdaIy">ዓምደ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ በድል፡ ናኝ፡</persName> reigned for five years.</p>
                              <p>
                                 <persName xml:lang="gez" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10626ZaraY">ዘርአ፡ ያዕቆብ፡</persName> reigned for 34 years and two months. 
                       <q xml:lang="en">Under his reign there was a controversy about religion:
                         
                          <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4709Giyorgis">
                                       <t:roleName xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="title">ʾabbā</t:roleName>
                                    </persName> 
                                    <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4709Giyorgis">Giyorgis of Saglā</persName>
                          had a discussion with a European and then wrote 
                         <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1952Mashaf">Maṣḥafa mǝśṭir</ref>. Furthermore, a heathen from the land of <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC1095Adal">ʾAdāl</placeName> called
                          <persName xml:lang="gez" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11953Badlay">በድላይ፡</persName>, who completely ressembled <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11293Goliath">Goliath</persName> the Philistine,
                          came to fight him. He <supplied reason="explanation" resp="PRS10747Zotenbe">the king</supplied> defeated him,
                         killed him and obtained all his possessions. By the power of his allmighty God he let no enemy
                         survive.
                       </q>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                 <persName xml:lang="gez" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS2334BaedaM">በእደ፡ ማርያም፡</persName>
                                 <q xml:lang="gez">ወሥዕሉኒ፡ ሀለወ፡ በአቶሮንሰ፡ ማርያም፡</q>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                 <persName xml:lang="gez" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS3874eskender">እስክንድር፡</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                 <persName xml:lang="gez" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7481NaodA">ናዖድ፡</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                 <persName xml:lang="gez" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6229LebnaDe">ወናግ፡ ሰገድ፡</persName>
                              </p>
                           </note>
                        </msItem>
                      
